The Management Caretaker Committee Chairman in Barkin Ladi Local Government Area of Plateau State, Mr. Ezekiel Mandyau is dead. DAILY POST gathered that the Council chairman died at the Jos University Teaching Hospital on Thursday evening after a brief illness. His demise was confirmed by Leader of Barkin Ladi Legislative Council, Mr. Pam Chollom Dung, in Jos on Thursday night. Dung said, ” It’s true, we were with him in the morning and he was also with some people in the afternoon and there was no problem. “Later, we heard that they took him to the hospital only for us to hear this evening that he has passed on. It’s really sad”. Reacting to the incident, State Secretary of the All Progressives Congress in the State, Bashir Sati, who also confirmed the death of the Council chairman, described his death as “shocking”, saying the party and the people of the state would greatly miss him